hise history and their 24th in [[Atlanta]].\n==Offseason==\n* December 23, 1988: [[Darrell Evans]] was signed as a free agent by the Braves.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/e/evansda01.shtml Darrell Evans page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* March 29, 1989: [[Mark Eichhorn]] was purchased by the Atlanta Braves from the Toronto Blue Jays. <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/e/eichhma01.shtml|title= Mark Eichhorn: Career Statistics |publisher= Baseball Reference| accessdate= 16 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Regular season==\n\n===Season standings===\n{{1989 NL West standings}}\n\n===Record vs. opponents===\n{{1989 NL Record vs. opponents|team=ATL}}\n\n===Opening Day starters===\n*[[Ger\u00f3nimo Berroa]]\n*Jeff Blauser\n*[[Jody Davis (baseball)|Jody Davis]]\n*Ron Gant\n*Tom Glavine\n*Dale Murphy\n*Gerald Perry\n*Lonnie Smith\n*[[Andr\u00e9s Thomas]]<ref>http://baseball-almanac.com/teamstats/roster.php?y=1989&t=ATL</ref>\n\n===Notable transactions===\n* July 2, 1989: [[Zane Smith]] was traded by the Braves to the [[Montreal Expos]] for [[Sergio Valdez]], [[Nate Minchey]], and Kevin Dean (minors).<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/s/smithza01.shtml Zane Smith page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* August 12, 1989: [[Ed Romero]] was signed as a free agent by the Braves.<ref name=romero>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/r/romered01.shtml Ed Romero page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* August 23, 1989: Ed Romero was traded by the Braves to the [[Milwaukee Brewers]] for a player to be named later. The Brewers completed the deal by sending [[Jay Aldrich]] to the Braves on September 1.<ref name=romero />\n* August 24, 1989: [[Jim Acker]] was traded by the Braves to the [[Toronto Blue Jays]] for [[Tony Castillo (pitcher)|Tony Castillo]] and [[Francisco Cabrera (baseball)|Francisco Cabrera]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/c/cabrefr01.shtml Francisco Cabrera page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* August 24, 1989: [[Paul Assenmacher]]