88 World Series home run|pinch-hit game winning homer]] in the first game off of [[Dennis Eckersley]] and the continued mastery of series MVP [[Orel Hershiser]].\n\n===Postseason Game log===\n{| class=\"toccolours collapsible\" width=90% style=\"clear:both; margin:1.5em auto; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=2 style=\"{{Baseball primary style|Los Angeles Dodgers}}\" | 1988 Postseason (8\u20134)\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|<div class=\"NavFrame collapsed \">\n<div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"{{Baseball primary style|Los Angeles Dodgers}}\">National League Championship Series (4\u20133)</div>\n<div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"text-align:center;\">\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"4%\" | Game\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"11%\" | Date\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"11%\" | Opponent\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"8%\" | Score\n!bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"14%\" | Win\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"14%\" | Loss\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"14%\" | Save\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"8%\" | Attendance\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"5%\" | Series\n|-  bgcolor=\"ffbbbb\"\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"ffbbbb\"\n| 1 || October 4 || [[1988 New York Mets season|Mets]] || L 2\u20133 || [[Randy Myers|Myers]] (1\u20130) || '''[[Jay Howell|Howell]]''' (0\u20131) || || 55,582 || 0\u20131\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"bbffbb\"\n| 2 || October 5 || [[1988 New York Mets season|Mets]] || '''W''' 6\u20133 || '''[[Tim Belcher|Belcher]]''' (1\u20130) || [[David Cone|Cone]] (0\u20131) || '''[[Alejandro Pe\u00f1a|Pe\u00f1a]]''' (1) || 55,780 || 1\u20131\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"bbbbbb\"\n| || October 7 || @ [[1988 New York Mets season|Mets]] || colspan=\"6\"|''Postponed (rain), rescheduled for October 8''\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"ffbbbb\"\n| 3 || October 8 || @ [[1988 New York Mets season|Mets]] || L 4\u20138 || [[Randy Myers|Myers]] (2\u20130) || '''[[Alejandro Pe\u00f1a|Pe\u00f1a]]''' (0\u20131) || || 44