988 Oakland Athletics season|Athletics]] || L 1\u20132 || [[Rick Honeycutt|Honeycutt]] (1\u20130) || '''[[Jay Howell|Howell]]''' (0\u20131) || || 49,316 || 2-1\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"bbffbb\"\n| 4 || October 19 || @ [[1988 Oakland Athletics season|Athletics]] || '''W''' 4\u20133 || '''[[Tim Belcher|Belcher]]''' (1\u20130) || [[Dave Stewart (baseball)|Stewart]] (0\u20131) || '''[[Jay Howell|Howell]]''' (1) || 49,317 || 3\u20131\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"bbffbb\"\n| 5 || October 20 || @ [[1988 Oakland Athletics season|Athletics]] || '''W''' 5\u20132 || '''[[Orel Hershiser|Hershiser]]''' (2\u20130) || [[Storm Davis|Davis]] (0\u20132) || || 49,317 || 4\u20131\n|}</div></div>\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n*[[1988 Major League Baseball All-Star Game]]\n**[[Orel Hershiser]] reserve\n* [[Major League Baseball Most Valuable Player Award|National League Most Valuable Player Award]]\n**[[Kirk Gibson]]\n* [[Cy Young Award]]\n**[[Orel Hershiser]]\n* [[Manager of the Year Award]]\n**[[Tommy Lasorda]]\n*[[1988 National League Championship Series|National League Championship MVP]]\n**[[Orel Hershiser]]\n*[[World Series Most Valuable Player]]\n**[[Orel Hershiser]]\n*[[Gold Glove Award]]\n**[[Orel Hershiser]]\n*[[MLB Comeback Player of the Year Award|Comeback Player of the Year Award]]\n**[[Tim Leary (baseball)|Tim Leary]]\n*[[Baseball Digest|Baseball Digest Rookie All-Star]]\n**[[Tim Belcher]]\n*[[The Sporting News Manager of the Year Award|TSN Manager of the Year Award]]\n**[[Tommy Lasorda]]\n{{col-2}}\n*[[Sporting News|TSN Executive of the Year Award]]\n**[[Fred Claire]]\n*[[The Sporting News Rookie of the Year Award|TSN Rookie Pitcher of the Year Award]]\n**[[Tim Belcher]]\n*[[The Sporting News Pitcher of the Year Award|TSN Pitcher of the Year Award]]\n**[[Orel Hershiser]]\n*[[Silver Slugger Award]]\n**[[Tim Leary (baseball)|Tim Leary]]\n**[[Kirk Gibson]]\n*[[The Sporting News Player of the Year Award|TSN Major League Player of the Year Award]]\n**[[Orel Hershiser]]\n*[[Sporting News|TSN National League All-Star]]\n**[[Orel Hershiser]]\n*[[Pitcher of the Month|NL Pitcher of the Month]]\n**[[Orel Hershiser]] (April 1988)\n**[[Orel Hershiser]] (September 1988)\n*[[NL Player of the Week]]\n**[[Kal Daniels]] (Apr. 4\u201310)\n**[[Tim Leary (baseball)|Tim Leary]] (July 18\u201324)\n**[[Orel Hershiser]] (Sep. 26-Oct.2)\n{{col-end}}\n\n== Farm system ==\n{{MLB Farm System\n| level14   = [[Triple-A (baseball)|AAA]]\n| team14    = [[Albuquerque Dukes]]\n| league14  = [[Pacific Coast League]]\n| manager14 = [[Terry Collins]]\n| level15   = [[Double-A (baseball)|AA]]\n| team15    = [[San Antonio Missions]]\n| league15  = [[Texas League]]\n| manager15 = [[Kevin Kennedy (baseball)|Kevin Kennedy]]\n| level16   = [[Class A-Advanced|High A]]\n| team16    = [[Bakersfield Blaze|Bakersfield Dodgers]]\n| league16  = [[California League]]\n| manager16 = [[Gary LaRocque]]\n| level17   = [[Class A-Advanced|High A]]\n| team17    = [[Vero Beach Devil Rays|Vero Beach Dodgers]]\n| league17  = [[Florida State League]]\n| manager17 = [[John Shoemaker]]\n| level18   = [[Class A-Short Season|A-Short Season]]\n| team18    = [[Salem Dodgers]]\n| league18  = [[Northwest League]]\n| manager18 = Tom Beyers\n| level19   = '''[[Rookie League|Rookie]]'''\n| team19    = '''[[Great Falls Voyagers|Great Falls Dodgers]]'''\n| league19  = ''' [[Pioneer League (baseball)|Pioneer League]]'''\n| manager19 = '''[[Tim Johnson (baseball)|Tim Johnson]]'''\n| level20   = [[Rookie League|Rookie]]\n| team20    = [[Arizona League Dodgers|Gulf Coast Dodgers]]\n| league20  = [[Gulf Coast League]]\n| manager20 = Joe Alvarez\n}}\n\nTeams in '''BOLD''' won League Championships\n\n==Major League Baseball Draft==\n{{Main|1988 Major League Baseball Draft}}\n\nThe Dodgers drafted 62 players in this draft. Of those, 11 of them would eventually play Major League baseball. The Dodgers lost their second round pick to the [[Oakland Athletics]] as compensation for their signing free agent outfielder [[Mike Davis (baseball)|Mike Davis]].\n\nThe top pick in the draft was Pitcher Bill Bene out of [[California State University, Los Angeles]]. In nine seasons in the Minors he had a record of 18-34 with a 5.45 ERA in 252 games (49 starts). In 2012, he was arrested and sentenced to six months in prison for operating a counterfeit [[karaoke]] business and failing to pay federal taxes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailynews.com/general-news/20120924/ex-dodgers-pitcher-bill-bene-gets-6-months-in-jail-for-dodging-taxes|title=Ex-Dodgers pitcher Bill Bene gets 6 months in jail for dodging taxes|work=LA Daily News|date=September 23, 2012|accessdate=November 6, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141107015837/http://www.dailynews.com/general-news/20120924/ex-dodgers-pitcher-bill-bene-gets-6-months-in-jail-for-dodging-taxes|archive-date=November 7, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThis draft produced two of the Dodgers top players of the 1990s. In the sixth round they selected first baseman [[Eric Karros]] from [[University of California, Los Angeles|UCLA]]. The 1992 Rookie of the Year and a 1995 Silver Slugger Award winner, Karros hit .268 with 284 homers and 1,027 RBI in 14 seasons (12 of them with the Dodgers) and is the L.A. Dodgers all-time home run leader.\n\nIn the 62nd round with their last pick of the draft the Dodgers selected [[Mike Piazza]] from [[Miami Dade College]] as a favor to his god-father, manager [[Tommy Lasorda]]. Piazza would win the 1993 Rookie of the Year Award and was a 12 time All-Star and 10 time Silver Slugger Award winner in his 16 seasons (mostly with the Dodgers and [[New York Mets]]). He hit .308 with 427 home runs and 1,335 RBI.\n{| class=\"toccolours collapsible collapsed\" style=\"width:100%; background:inherit\"\n|-\n! 1988 Draft Picks\n|-\n|\n<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/draft/?query_type=franch_year&team_ID=LAD&year_ID=1988&draft_type=junreg& 1988 Los Angeles Dodgers Picks in the MLB June Amateur 